# Module 1: Basic Electrical Circuits

## Segment 1: Fundamentals of Electricity

### Objective 1: Define Electricity and Give an Application
Electricity is the flow of electrons (tiny charged particles) through wires—similar to water moving through pipes.  
**Application:** Turning on a lamp lets electricity light up your room.  
**Videos:**  
- [What is electricity? - Electricity Explained](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ru032Mfsfig)  
- [What is Electricity? - Science for Kids](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t09pAwLICC4)  

### Objective 2: Describe Two Types of Electrical Current and Give an Application of Each
- **Direct Current (DC):** Flows one way (batteries—phones, flashlights).
- **Alternating Current (AC):** Goes back and forth (wall outlets—microwaves, TVs).
**Example:** Toys use DC; refrigerators use AC.
**Videos:**  
- [Types of Electric Current](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vXW42TRIq1Y)  
- [Types of Electric Current | Nagwa](https://www.nagwa.com/en/videos/807126795808/)  

### Objective 3: Describe the Function and Operation of a Circuit Tester
A circuit tester checks if electricity is present—like a detective looking for power.
**Example:** Plug into an outlet to see if it works.
**Videos:**  
- [How To Use a Voltage Tester (Ask This Old House)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0groxS9MaSw)  
- [How Best To Use Non-Contact Voltage Testers](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gL5LQmL7WTk)  

---

## Segment 2: Electrical Circuit Components

### Objective 4: Describe the Function of Four Basic Components
- **Power Source:** Gives energy (battery, wall outlet).
- **Conductors:** Let electricity flow (wires).
- **Load:** Uses energy (lights, motors).
- **Control Devices:** Turn electricity on/off (switch).
**Analogy:** Like a water park—pump, pipes, fountains, and valves.
**Videos:**  
- [Basic Electronic Components Explained](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLKDDPHypZkIU4EdJ0UdyvIx_GqzEmUMfM)  
- [Basic Electrical Components Symbols & Functions](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dz89cfA6ssc)  

### Objective 5: Describe the Operation of Two Types of Power Supplies and Their Schematic Symbols
- **Battery (DC):** Powers remotes/phones.
- **Adapter (AC to DC):** Powers laptops.
**Videos:**  
- [Every Component of a Switch Mode Power Supply Explained](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3FyXqNcqvRM)  
- [Power Supply Setup & Assembly](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AyDzpQsxKlc)  

### Objective 6: Describe the Function of an Electrical Schematic
A schematic is a diagram showing how parts connect—like a treasure map for electricians.
**Example:** Used to wire houses or fix electronics.
**Videos:**  
- [Schematic Diagrams & Symbols, Electrical Circuits](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dl1gFBNa0Ik)  
- [How to Read Electrical Diagrams](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GHhcyH99inE)  

---

## Segment 3: Manual Input Devices

### Objective 7: Describe the Operation of a Manual Switch
Manual switches are gates for electricity—flip, press, or turn to control flow.
**Videos:**  
- [Types of Electrical Switches](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AbqGWNIItTo)  

### Objective 8: Describe N.O. and N.C. Contacts and Schematic Symbols
- **Normally Open:** Electricity flows when pressed.
- **Normally Closed:** Electricity stops when pressed.
**Videos:**  
- [NO NC Contact in PLC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B0tuMyJ5Eqc)  
- [Push Buttons Explained: NO vs NC](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o5FzuijyvRs)  

### Objective 9: Function of Three Types of Manual Switch Operators and Give an Application
- **Toggle:** Light switches.
- **Pushbutton:** Doorbells, crosswalks.
- **Rotary:** Stove knobs.
**Videos:**  
- [Selector Switch Explained in Animation](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dp4UfhuTczA)  
- [Different Types of Electrical Switches](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E6AicGQk9po)  

---

## Segment 4: Output Devices

### Objective 11: Describe Five Types of Electrical Output Devices and an Application
- **Lamp:** Lights rooms.
- **Buzzer:** Sounds alarms.
- **Motor:** Runs fans.
- **Solenoid:** Locks doors.
- **Relay:** Switches circuits.
**Videos:**  
- [GRADE 8: Output Devices (Buzzers, LEDs, Motors)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HZvtyT2RoH0)  
- [Output Devices: Importance & Examples](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hZAHw4hYqmg)  

### Objective 12: Output Device Symbols
**Videos:**  
- [100+ Electrical & Electronic Circuit Symbols](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ecvoex7vl4A)  

